ddle, and AI services on the top. This isn=E2=80=99t some grand insight: it=
 follows the core structure of cloud computing:

* Infrastructure-as-a-Service (IaaS) is on the bottom; this is basically re=
nting servers.
* Platform-as-a-Service (PaaS) is in the middle; this abstracts away the se=
rvers letting you build on an API. PaaS can be built on IaaS.
* Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) is on top; these are the actual applications=
 that end users use (and which are built on top of the PaaS or IaaS layers)=
.

AWS started with IaaS and has moved up to PaaS, as I detailed yesterday; Mi=
crosoft has a massive franchise (formerly called Office) in SaaS, got tract=
ion with IaaS for its enterprise customers, and has been catching up in Paa=
S.

AI PaaS and SaaS
----------------

That=E2=80=99s a lot of acronyms, but the relevant takeaway is this: Q sits=
