_nTDbM )

In this case, the fact this is the same level as SaaS in the traditional cl=
oud stack is very pertinent; Q is a SaaS application, that needs access to =
other SaaS applications to be useful:

Q integrates with other SaaS applications ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=
=3DPMfn9_nTDbM )

The challenge, of course, is that it isn=E2=80=99t integrated with those ot=
her applications in the way that Microsoft Copilot is integrated with Micro=
soft 365 applications and the =E2=80=9CMicrosoft Graph=E2=80=9D; it seems f=
air to assume that Microsoft=E2=80=99s strength in the SaaS layer will like=
ly translate to strength in the same layer when it comes to AI. What Q does=
 have going for it is that it is cheaper: $20/user per month as compared to=
 Copilot=E2=80=99s pricing of $30/month.

What remains to be seen is if it is any good: Microsoft has to date benefit=
ed from its association with OpenAI, but Selipsky, much as he did in the co=
mment I highlighted yesterday, sought to frame that association as a liabil=
ity:

( https://videopress.com/embed/e1t0m35A?hd=3D1&cover=3D1&loop=3D0&autoPlay=
